  "prob_desc_description": "Greatest common divisor GCD(a, b) of two positive integers a and b is equal to the biggest integer d such that both integers a and b are divisible by d. There are many efficient algorithms to find greatest common divisor GCD(a, b), for example, Euclid algorithm. Formally, find the biggest integer d, such that all integers a, a + 1, a + 2, ..., b are divisible by d. To make the problem even more complicated we allow a and b to be up to googol, 10100 — such number do not fit even in 64-bit integer type!",
